    name: "Eastern Orthodoxy",
    summary:
      "The oldest continuously practicing form of Christianity, centered on divine liturgy, theosis (becoming like God), icons, and the seven ecumenical councils. It thinks in images where the West thinks in arguments.",
    lensTags: ["orthodox", "academic"],
